<br>
I understand the concept of crime and punishment.  What eludes me, however, is how someone else's sacrifice (if it can be called that) would offset own sins.  A judge sentences criminals -- not people who knew the criminals, but had nothing to do with their crimes.  It is an ill-fitting analogy.<br>
<br>
As a parent, would you willfully watch one of your children suffer as a means for forgiving an act of disobedience by your other children?  It makes no sense.  So why would an all-knowing, all-loving god find this appropriate?<br>
